<FIRST>r a PM-Lites     07-08 0351</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lites,0362</SECOND>
<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>McKEES ROCKS, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Buster was going to serve as ring
bearer, but now he's being treated like a dog and he's out of the
wedding.
   A 10-month-old Samoyed, the dog was scheduled to participate at
today's wedding of his masters, Tracy Galentine and Val Finnell, at
Christ Community Church in this Pittsburgh suburb.
   The Rev. Cho Kim approved of the plan until church officials at a
United Methodist Church conference in Grove City, 50 miles to the
north, read a June 14 news story about Buster and the wedding and
expressed their misgivings to the minister.
   Kim changed her mind and now the groom's mother is annoyed.
   ``After all, how long is the dog going to be in that church?''
said Dolores Finnell. ``During biblical times, sheep were allowed at
the altar and in temples. I can't understand now what is wrong with
a dog.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>DOVER, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   After five litters of puppies, a Doberman
pinscher named Saber was ready for a change. So she took to nursing
a litter of kittens whose mother wanted no part of them.
   ``She didn't have any puppies of her own, so she just decided she
wanted the kittens,'' Linda Ferguson said of her 8-year-old dog who
has been using the milk from a false pregnancy to nurse five
2{-week-old kittens.
   The kittens' mother decided she would rather hunt than tend to
her new breed, leaving them hungry and weak. Before long, Mrs.
Ferguson said, Saber began snooping around the kittens and ``acting
kind of goofy.''
   Before the Fergusons knew it, Saber stepped in and took over.
When Mrs. Ferguson tried to put the kittens in with their natural
mother, her husband Gordy said, Saber ``just went berserk.''
   The dog now refuses to go on morning walks because, Mrs. Ferguson
believes, she doesn't want to let the kittens out of her sight.
   ``She's a lot more protective of these kittens than she ever was
about her puppies,'' Mrs. Ferguson said. ``She won't leave 'em. She
just won't. I haven't seen anything like it before.''
</TEXT>
