<HEAD>Four Killed In Ethnic-Related Shootings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rival student groups fought gunbattles
Saturday at Karachi University, and at least four people, including
a police officer, were killed, officials said.
   Hospital officials said another 13 people were treated for bullet
wounds.
   The clash was between the student wings of the Pakistan People's
Party and the Muhajir Quami Movement, which represents Indian
immigrants who fled to Pakistan at the time of partition in 1947.
   ``This morning, the university looked like a battlefield,'' a
witness said. ``Students carrying Kalashnikovs took positions and
fired at each other indiscriminately.''
   Authorities closed the university following the shooting.
   The Pakistan People's Party, headed by Prime Minister Benazir
Bhutto, took power following elections last November. It also rules
the southern Sind province, where hundreds of people have died in
ethnic violence.
