<FIRST>r i AM-Soviet-Nuclear     07-08 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Soviet-Nuclear,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviets Set Off Nuclear Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union detonated a nuclear device with a
force of 20 kilotons on Saturday at its test site in Semipalatinsk
in Kazakhstan, the official news agency Tass reported.
   ``The test was carried out for the purpose of upgrading military
hardware,'' the report said. ``Radiation levels at and outside the
test-site were within the norm.''
   The detonation occurred at 7:47 a.m., Tass said.
   A kiloton has the explosive force of 1,000 pounds of TNT. The
atomic bomb dropped Aug. 6, 1945, on Hiroshima, Japan, in the first
use of the bomb as a weapon had the explosive force of 20 kilotons.
</TEXT>
