<SECOND>AM-BRF--Graceland Record,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>Attendance Mark Set July 3</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Graceland, Elvis Presley's home, set a
one-day attendance on July 3 of 4,920 guests _ bringing in more
money than Presley paid for the mansion in 1957, officials said.
   The previous one-day viewing record was 4,771 set July 4 a year
ago.
   ``I always get a kick out of things like this,'' said Jack Soden,
Graceland executive director. ``I remember when I came here how
people said it would never work or would only last a couple years.''
   Soden said visitors on Monday spent $110,000 on tour tickets and
in the Graceland-operated shops. Presley paid $103,000 for the the
big house in 1957. It opened for tours in 1982.
   Presley, ``the king of rock 'n' roll,'' died of heart disease at
his home on Aug. 16, 1977.
