<FIRST>r a AM-TattooedRobber     07-08 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Tattooed Robber,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Robber's Tattooed Rose Is Hardly Unique, Police Find</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORTH RICHLAND HILLS, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police in this Fort Worth
suburb learned the hard way that a rose tattoo on a woman's bustline
should not necessarily be considered a unique distinguishing mark.
   Police told the Fort Worth Star-Telegram on Wednesday that they
were looking for a woman with a rose tattoo on her left breast who
is suspected of robbing a gas station of $8,500.
   After the paper published the information Thursday, about 300
people called police to say they knew of such a woman.
   ``I've handled at least 55 calls myself,'' said police detective
Cliff Jaynes. ``Every woman with a red rose on her has been snitched
on.''
   Police decided to release more information about the robbery
suspect that should nip further calls in the bud, the newspaper said
Saturday.
   The woman has another tattoo: a crude letter ``S'' with two
horizontal slash marks on her left forearm.
</TEXT>
